<style>
  .faq-item .answer {
    display: none;
  }
  .faq-item.open .answer {
    display: block;
  }
</style>

<div class="w-full">
    <h2 class="text-2xl text-center mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div id="faq-container">
        <div class="faq-item border-b border-gray-200 py-4">
            <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center">
                <h3 class="font-semibold">How do I create a new ticket?</h3>
                <span class="toggle-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="answer mt-2 text-gray-600">
                <p>
                    To create a new ticket, simply click the "Add Ticket" button on your dashboard and fill out
                    the required fields.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item border-b border-gray-200 py-4">
            <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center">
                <h3 class="font-semibold">Can I customize the ticket statuses?</h3>
                <span class="toggle-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="answer mt-2 text-gray-600">
                <p>
                    Yes, you can customize the ticket statuses to fit your team's workflow in the settings
                    panel.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item border-b border-gray-200 py-4">
            <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center">
                <h3 class="font-semibold">Is there a mobile app?</h3>
                <span class="toggle-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="answer mt-2 text-gray-600">
                <p>
                    Currently, we have a responsive web application that works great on all devices. A native
                    mobile app is on our roadmap.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item border-b border-gray-200 py-4">
            <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center">
                <h3 class="font-semibold">How can I track the progress of my tickets?</h3>
                <span class="toggle-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="answer mt-2 text-gray-600">
                <p>
                    You can track the progress of your tickets on the main dashboard, which provides real-time
                    updates and status indicators for every ticket.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
        const faqContainer = document.getElementById('faq-container');
        faqContainer.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
            const button = e.target.closest('button');
            if (button) {
                const item = button.parentElement;
                const answer = item.querySelector('.answer');
                const icon = item.querySelector('.toggle-icon');

                if (item.classList.contains('open')) {
                    item.classList.remove('open');
                    icon.textContent = '+';
                } else {
                    item.classList.add('open');
                    icon.textContent = '-';
                }
            }
        });
    });
</script>